7: It reminds me of our past.
10:
On nights when even the mountains
seem to freeze, the stars shine all
the brighter... That is why you chose
the coldest night, correct?
13:
I was worried tonight would be a
disappointment... Starview is so
warm, after all.
16:
We certainly have come a long way,
haven't we?
17:
Thinking back on it now, it's almost
surprising that we're able to carry on
as we do.
29: I'm sorry... I'm so sorry! I—
42:
I've thought long and hard about
what I would do when I saw you
again... What I should do...
44:
But no longer. I have made my
decision!
47:
I will never force you onto the
battlefield again. I will protect you!
51:
But... But I... I abandoned all those
people—
55:
It doesn't matter... They don't matter,
Lady Phiria. You should never have
been forced to fight...
57:
Let us gaze upon the stars again
sometime...
66:
Despite all that, you chose to enter
the battlefield once again. But this
time, you were driven by your own
hopes and dreams.
76:
I am simply stating that my role as
your protector has come to an end.
79:
You are strong, Lady Phiria. Strong
enough to move forward on your
own. You no longer require my
assistance.
87:
I-I made a vow. I promised myself
that I would protect the wind that
blows through Starview!
89:
I wish to create a place where my
loved ones and I can live together in
peace!
92:
S-so... If I can't be with you, Cecilia,
then... Then my dream can't come
true!
96:
In that case, we will achieve that
dream together.
103:
Instead of your knight, what if I was
your comrade? Someone who could
stand beside you.
105: Lady Phiria, will you be my friend?
109:
Yes... Of course I will! We're already
friends, after all!
115:
Man, you really saved my bacon! I
really appreciate you helping us out!
118:
Think nothing of it. I am used to
patrolling, after all. Make use of me
in whatever capacity you see fit.
127:
Ah, greetings, you two. It seems the
festival was in need of more
security, so I came to offer my
services.
134:
I wish to expand my horizons, so I
thought starting with a task I am
familiar with and branching out
from there would be an effective
strategy.
136:
After all, I have already decided I will
never return to my homeland.
139:
I do not know what the Star Augurs
were thinking...
143:
However, I am now certain that their
methods conflict with my own
ideals. I will never return to their side.
147:
I see... You truly are a courageous
woman, Cecilia.
150:
To be fair, even if I did wish to return,
we have yet to find our world
anyway.
152:
And if one wishes to eat, they must
earn their keep.
157:
Gotcha... Is that why Phiria was in
the library studying before?
163:
Hehe... She's a strong one, is she
not? I have my work cut out for me if
I wish to keep up with her.
167:
We were just about to accept a
request from the Guild ourselves.
Would you perhaps like to form a
party?
170: Yes, it would be an honor!
